{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_2","type":"command_execution","command":"/bin/bash -lc \"sed -n '1,220p' task-plans/prompt-rule-memo-cards-task-plan.md\"","aggregated_output":"# Prompt Rule Memo Cards Task Plan\n\n## Priority\n\nPriority 2\n\n## Objective\n\nTurn the extension into a working memory system, not only a launcher.\n\n## Scope\n\n- prompt cards\n- rule cards\n- memo cards\n- visibility of `prompt.md`, `ROADMAP.md`, and related loop files\n\n## Tasks\n\n### Task 1 — Card Types\n\n- define first-class card types for prompt, rule, memo\n- distinguish them visually from agent cards\n\n### Task 2 — Source Integration\n\n- connect cards to files such as `prompt.md`, `ROADMAP.md`, and local notes\n- support lightweight editing or quick-open behavior\n\n### Task 3 — Workflow Integration\n\n- allow agent cards to reference relevant prompt/rule/memo cards\n- surface the right context beside active work\n\n## Exit Criteria\n\n- users can keep rules and prompts visible inside the agent center\n- memory artifacts are not buried in separate files or tabs\n","exit_code":0,"status":"completed"}}
